{
  "texts": [
    "NIST has begun a process to solicit, evaluate, and standardize schemes providing authenticated encryption with associated data (AEAD) and optional hashing functionalities for constrained environments where the performance of current NIST cryptographic standards is not acceptable.",
    "This follows two workshops and discussions with stakeholders from industry, government, and academia.",
    "A request for algorithms, including specifications, a selection procedure, and assessment criteria, was released by NIST in 2018 [37].",
    "In the first round of the standardisation process, NIST received 57 proposals in March 2019.",
    "With the introduction of Round 1 in April 2019, the NIST initiated the first phase of their standardisation process for lightweight cryptography."
  ]
}